---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Drink & Listen — The Layer Atami"
  description="Coffee, drinks, music, and something sweet. The Layer's public spaces in Atami — Lobby Bar Taki, Coffee Kissaten Tampopo, and Dandelion Record Kissaten."
>
  <div class="page-header container">
    <p class="page-header__label">Drink & Listen</p>
    <h1>Coffee, drinks, music,<br />and something sweet.</h1>
    <p class="page-header__sub">
      Alongside our stays, The Layer in Atami is home to public spaces for listening and lingering.
      Each space has its own approach to sound, its own rhythm, and a small sweet made to sit alongside a drink.
      No full meals — just the things that make an afternoon or an evening worth staying for.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="spaces container">
    <article class="space" id="taki">
      <div class="space__image">
        <img
          src="/images/amenities.jpg"
          alt="Lobby Bar Taki at The Layer Atami — records, drinks, and listening"
          width="800"
          height="900"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="space__body">
        <p class="space__label">Evening · Bar</p>
        <h2>Lobby Bar Taki</h2>
        <p class="space__tagline">Shaped by physical media, shared listening, and sweets.</p>
        <p>
          Taki is home to our record and CD collection, played intentionally through the night.
          The bar is built around the idea that music listened to together — in a room, from a
          speaker you can see — is different from music listened to alone.
        </p>
        <p>
          Alongside drinks, we offer a small house sweet: cookie ice cream sandwiches.
          Something playful and nostalgic, best enjoyed with good sound and good company.
        </p>
        <dl class="space__details">
          <dt>When</dt>
          <dd>Evening hours</dd>
          <dt>Sound</dt>
          <dd>Records & CDs, played intentionally</dd>
          <dt>Sweet</dt>
          <dd>Cookie ice cream sandwiches</dd>
          <dt>Location</dt>
          <dd>The Layer Atami Hotel lobby, Atami</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="space space--reverse" id="tampopo">
      <div class="space__image space__image--light">
        <div class="space__placeholder" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="space__body">
        <p class="space__label">Daytime · Coffee</p>
        <h2>Coffee Kissaten Tampopo</h2>
        <p class="space__tagline">A daytime kissaten for coffee and conversation.</p>
        <p>
          Tampopo celebrates Atami's long history of kissaten — the sit-and-stay coffee culture
          that defined Japanese café life for decades. The space evolved from our original coffee
          corner into a communal seating area that invites guests and visitors to slow down,
          order well, and stay a little longer than planned.
        </p>
        <p>
          Contemporary coffee alongside kissaten classics, and a sweet treat. The pace is the point.
        </p>
        <dl class="space__details">
          <dt>When</dt>
          <dd>Daytime hours</dd>
          <dt>Coffee</dt>
          <dd>Contemporary & kissaten classics</dd>
          <dt>Atmosphere</dt>
          <dd>Communal, unhurried</dd>
          <dt>Location</dt>
          <dd>The Layer Atami Hotel, Atami</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="space" id="dandelion">
      <div class="space__image space__image--light">
        <div class="space__placeholder" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="space__body">
        <p class="space__label">Record Kissaten · Tenant</p>
        <h2>Dandelion Record Kissaten</h2>
        <p class="space__tagline">A record listening space with its own sensibility.</p>
        <p>
          Dandelion is a tenant-run record kissaten housed within The Layer Atami.
          It has its own collection, its own curatorial voice, and its own approach to the
          listening space.
        </p>
        <p class="space__tbd">Full details to follow as we get closer to opening.</p>
        <dl class="space__details">
          <dt>Format</dt>
          <dd>Tenant-run record kissaten</dd>
          <dt>Status</dt>
          <dd>Details coming</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>

  <section class="drink-note container">
    <p>
      All three spaces are public-facing and welcome guests, visitors, and anyone passing through Atami.
      None serve full meals. Reservations are not required for drop-in visits.
    </p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn">Questions? Get in touch</a>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding-block: 4rem 1rem;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .page-header__label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .page-header__sub {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    opacity: 0.7;
    max-width: 620px;
  }

  .spaces {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6rem;
    padding-block: 4rem 5rem;
  }

  .space {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .space--reverse { direction: rtl; }
  .space--reverse > * { direction: ltr; }

  .space__image {
    aspect-ratio: 3/4;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #1c2d1d;
    border-radius: 80px;
  }
  .space__image img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; }
  .space__image--light { background: #e8e4df; }
  .space__placeholder { width: 100%; height: 100%; }

  .space__label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .space__body h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .space__tagline {
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .space__body p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    opacity: 0.75;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: 520px;
  }
  .space__tbd { opacity: 0.55 !important; }

  .space__details {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
  }
  .space__details dt {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    opacity: 0.45;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .space__details dd {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .drink-note {
    padding-block: 3rem 5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .drink-note p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    opacity: 0.65;
    max-width: 560px;
    flex: 1;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1.5px solid #213129;
    color: #213129;
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .btn:hover { background: #213129; color: #fff; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .space, .space--reverse {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
      direction: ltr;
    }
    .space__image { aspect-ratio: 16/9; }
  }
</style>
